Author: zatJUM#9924
Content: Are success swaps filtered like this?```curl --url "http://127.0.0.1:7783" --data "{\"userpass\":\"$userpass\",\"method\":\"my_recent_swaps\"}" | jq -c '.result | .swaps | .[] | select(.success_events[8]=="Finished")'```

Author: cipi#4502
Content: `success_events` and `error_events` are just a list of all possible success/error event types that are possible

Author: cipi#4502
Content: not the ones that actually occured in the swap

Author: zatJUM#9924
Content: So how do I filter finished swaps?

Author: cipi#4502
Content:
finished =! successfull
you need to check if one of the events of the swap is of type `error_events`, if so the swap failed
